              <gloss><p xml:id='OTPSD25004996P0'>Established around 1857, Moody, O'Ferrall &amp; Company was a cotton factor business owned by L. B. Moody, John W. O'Ferrall, and A. A. Payne in Enterprise, Mississippi. The company was very successful, becoming one of the biggest cotton trading businesses in eastern Mississippi, until military operations during the Civil War disrupted cotton sales. The partnership apparently ended around 1866. (<hi rend='italic'>The Times-Picayune</hi>, New Orleans, LA, December 13, 1895; <hi rend='italic'>Reports of Cases Argued and Determined in the Supreme Court, High Court of Errors and Appeals, and the Superior Court of Chancery of Mississippi, Book 22</hi>, 49–50)
